[[File:Partition_of_Cieszyn_Silesia.svg|thumb]] [[File:Presentation of Těšínské Slezsko at Regiontour 2010.jpg|thumb|Presentation of the Euroregion in Brno (2010)]] '''Euroregion Cieszyn Silesia''' ({{lang-pl|Euroregion Śląsk Cieszyński}}, {{lang-cs|Euroregion Těšínské Slezsko}}) is one of the [[euroregion]]s (transnational co-operation structures) between [[Poland]] and [[Czech Republic]]. It has area of about 1,400 km² and more than 680,000 inhabitants. The largest cities are [[Jastrzębie Zdrój]] from Polish side and [[Havířov]] from Czech side. It was established on 22 April 1998.<ref name="ulotka">{{cite web|url = https://www.olza.pl%2Fpl%2Fpobierz%2Fplik%2F277%2Fulotka-informacyjna-euroregionu-slask-cieszynski-i-sriwr-olza.pdf|title=EUROREGION ŚLĄSK CIESZYŃSKI - Těšínské Slezsko W PIGUŁCE|pages=4-5|language=Polish}}</ref>
It comprises a large part of the historical region of [[Cieszyn Silesia]]: * in Poland: 12 municipalities of the [[Cieszyn County]], 2 municipalities of the [[Bielsko County]] ([[gmina Jaworze|Jaworze]] and [[gmina Jasienica|Jasienica]]), 1 municipality in [[Wodzisław County]] ([[Gmina Godów|Godów]]) and [[Jastrzębie Zdrój]] (however, the last two are not part of Cieszyn Silesia). * in the Czech Republic: 16 municipalities of the [[Karviná District]] and 24 municipalities in the eastern part of the [[Frýdek-Místek District]];<ref name="ulotka"/><ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.czso.cz/documents/10180/20536602/13720510.pdf/c808dd6c-03ce-4ba5-b07f-55fcb674038a?version=1.0|title=Euroregion TĚŠÍNSKÉ SLEZSKO. Seznam obcí tvořících euroregion v roce 2004|language=Czech}}</ref>
Not the whole area of the historical Cieszyn Silesia region belongs to the euroregion, mainly [[Bielsko]] and [[gmina Czechowice-Dziedzice|Czechowice-Dziedzice]] and [[Frýdek, Frýdek-Místek|Frýdek]] with its surroundings, east of the [[Ostravice]] river, which belong to the [[Euroregion Beskydy]].<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.czso.cz/documents/10180/20536602/13720511.pdf/0a76c06e-d273-4de1-b381-151c525b4b38?version=1.0|title=Euroregion Beskydy. Seznam obcí tvořících euroregion v roce 2004|year=2004|language=Czech}}</ref>
== Strategic goals of Euroregion == * wide development of the region * exchange of experience and information * support for culture, education and sport in the region * development of regional transport infrastructure * improvement of the security of citizens * tourism development * cooperation between schools and support for ecological initiatives
