[[Image:Oulu Market Hall 20070409.JPG|thumb|250px|Oulu Market Hall.]] The '''Oulu Market Square''' is the main [[market square]] of the city of [[Oulu]], [[Finland]].
The market square is located in the city centre, in the [[Pokkinen]] district, on the waterfront of the Oulujoki river. The [[Rotuaari]] pedestrian zone starts from the square behind the [[Toripolliisi]] statue.
In addition to the traditional market stalls, many old warehouses restored as bars and restaurants are bordering the square nowadays. The [[Oulu Market Hall|market hall]] was opened on the square in 1901 mainly to get selling of meat out of the open square.
