{{For|places named Sand Island|Sand Island (disambiguation)}} [[File:Fraser Island a04 indian head.jpg|thumb|The world's largest sand island, [[Fraser Island]], located along the coast of Australia]] A '''sand island''' is an [[island]] that is largely or completely made of [[sand]]. The largest sand island in the world is [[Fraser Island]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/heritage/places/world/fraser/information.html|title=World Heritage, Fraser Island|year=2008|author=Department of the Environment, Water, Heritage and the Arts|work=Australia}}</ref> Other examples of large sand islands are [[Moreton Island|Moreton]], [[North Stradbroke Island|North Stradbroke]] and [[Bribie Island|Bribie]], Islands which lie south of Fraser Island off the east coast of [[Australia]].
